headline: This S&P 500 Dividend Stock Is Down 71%, but Could Soar in 2025
summary: Retail companies have been through the gauntlet.  The pandemic, rising inflation, and the shift of consumer spending to travel and other services have pressured the stock performance of many retail companies.  The SPDR S&P Retail ETF has declined 9.6% over the past three years, underperforming the S&P 500's 26% return.
